				<h3>
					Career Aspect</h3>
				<p>
					I particularly am interested in working for the best team in order to learn to become the best where I could satisfy my ultimate career goal that I want to be technical excellence in Graphic Programming. Within the job, it will be great to have my daily work that allows me to expand my knowledge and explore new cutting-edge technologies through programming techniques especially in Graphics and Game Engine Development.</p>
				<p>
					I am a hard-worker and always contribute to the team with my full dedication. I love to share ideas, creativity and discuss interesting stuffs with others. It would be very cool if I could work with the team that has some sorts of similar mind-set and maybe share the same vision.</p>
				<p>
					Common to all excellent software engineers, I also often try to do my self-assessments and think about different ways to improve or polish my skills and very interested in my career development.&nbsp;For the company, a full support on an appropriate career progression would be one another most important thing that I concern as much as everything else. &nbsp;</p>
				<h3>
					Programming Skills</h3>
				<p>
					I believe that I am an excellent programmer as a top of the class with strong knowledge about maths and computer graphic. I have experienced working on most of the modern consoles, XBOX360/Kinect, PS3 and PC Direct3D 9/10. Currently I&rsquo;m accelerating myself into DirectX 11, spending my day-to-day experimenting with their new features and rendering pipeline, preparing for the next-gens.</p>
				<p>
					Through different projects, I also have been working with many in-house game engines on many aspects. Not only on the game itself, but also Tools, Build system and Third parties APIs.&nbsp;</p>
				<p>
					<a href="http://my-site:5000/cms/joomla17/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=70&amp;catid=11" title="CV ProgrammingSkill"><strong><span style="line-height: 21px;">Read more about my Programming Skills</span></strong></a></p>
				<p>
					Describing myself as a natural learner, I&#39;m constantly seeking myself new challenges to improve my technical expertise. I can study any new technologies in pace. On my spare time, I usually spend time on some researches of my personal interests. Most of the time these topics fall into some sorts of new tools and techniques implementation of the latest rendering technologies.</p>
				<h3>
					Work Experience</h3>
				<p>
					<em>Jun 2009-Present</em>: <strong>Reflections The Ubisoft Studio. Newcastle upon Tyne, UK.</strong><br />
					A graphic programmer, experienced working with a number of Game Engines. Familiar with the PS3, XBox360 and PC Direct3D developing environment. Specializing in GPU programming and GPU optimization.</p>
				<p>
					For the past year, I also have been involved in the Game Prototyping team, the job is to experiment Game engines, create and try some small game idea which might be suitable for XBLA or Web/Mobile Device. &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>
