					Demonstrator/Students Helper in <a href="http://my-site:5000/cms/joomla17//cms/joomla17/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=33&amp;catid=8&amp;Itemid=117" title="June 14-20, 2008 : Dare Schools Challenge'08">Dare Schools Challenge Project</a>, the annual game programming competition for high school students settled by Dundee city council and Abertay University. The main role is to help instructing the competitors to produce and complete their game applications.</p>
				<p>
					<em>Aug 2007, Oct 2008</em>: <strong>Dare to be Digital Ltd. Dundee, UK.</strong><br />
					Instruction Presenter working for <a href="http://my-site:5000/cms/joomla17//cms/joomla17/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=24&amp;catid=8&amp;Itemid=117" title="August 11-14, 2007 : Dare to be Digital Protoplay'07, Edinburgh">Dare to be Digital: Protoplay</a> Event. The main role is to demonstrate and present basic game programming techniques to guests and audiences during various exhibitions using SCRATCH software.</p>
				<p>
					<em>Nov 2002-2005</em>: <strong>Yokogawa Ltd. Bangkok, Thailand.</strong><br />
					Team Leader and System engineer, working in the Engineering department. The main role is to create and maintain real-time industrial process control applications. As a team lead of a small group of engineers, I have gained some good experience about team management, project planning and inter-communication skill.</p>
				<p>
					<em>Mar 2001-Jun 2001</em>: <strong>Sony Semiconductor Ltd. Bangkok, Thailand.</strong><br />
					Junior Test engineer working in the semiconductor production line. The main role is to create programs specially used in IC testers.</p>
				<h3>
					About me</h3>
				<div>
					I am a very friendly person and a real team player. At the studio, I&rsquo;m so called, &quot;that funny guy&quot;, who always bring smiles and energy to the team. Like a classic motto, I really play Hard but also work Hard too. I love to discuss and take initiative in bringing new interesting technology, and methods into development. I like spending time with Artists and Game designers learning and exchanging the idea about their professions.</div>
				<div>
					&nbsp;</div>
